// Regression: the entry's `#run` dispatches a map + systems DEFINED IN AN IMPORTED module (a non-entry
// compilation unit) across units. Under per-unit codegen the bodies emit in the module's own unit and the
// entry references them via the cross-unit declare path. Asserts the map actually mutated pool state, so
// it fails loudly if the declare ever regresses. Tested in BOTH whole-program AND incremental (per-unit) —
// the per-unit run is what broke when scheduled SYSTEMS/EACH lacked a cross-unit declare (only maps had one).
// RUN: %arche build -o %t %s && %t | grep -qF "n=1"
// RUN: %arche build --incremental -o %t.inc %s && %t.inc | grep -qF "n=1"
#import { "./run_helper_lib" }
#run seq({ mob_seed, bump, mob_report })
